The Life Esidimeni Arbitration hearing has resumed following a six-week long adjournment. Some of those still expected to testify in the next few days include former Gauteng Health MEC Qedani Mahlangu, Gauteng Premier David Makhura and Health Minister Aaron Motsoaledi. A hundred and forty three mentally-ill patients died after they were transferred to ill-equipped and unlicensed NGO’s.  That’s after the Gauteng Health Department abruptly terminated its long-standing contract with Life Esidimeni, saying it wanted to cut costs.  About SABC View all posts by SABC